N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 525.20 - Victims of human trafficking, presumption of physical injury

State Regulations

When a claimant applies as a victim of labor trafficking as
defined in section
135.35
of the Penal Law, or sex trafficking as defined in
section
230.34
of the Penal Law, there shall be a rebuttable presumption that
such victim has suffered a physical injury for the purposes of eligibility
under article 22 of the Executive Law. Notes
